<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4504896>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Synapsis puluongensis sp. nov. A–B – male, holotype. C–D – female, paratype. E – aedeagus, lateral view. F – aedeagus, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4504896/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4504898>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Morphological details of Synapsis species.A–B – elytral surface:A – S. puluongensis sp. nov. with elytral striae strongly and densely punctate and interval 2 not swollen; B – S. horaki Zídek & Pokorný, 2010, with elytral striae impunctate and interval 2 swollen. C–D – metafemora: C – S. puluongensis sp. nov.; D – S. yama Gillet, 1911. E–F – setation of hypomeral cavities: E – S. puluongensis sp. nov.; F – S. birmanica Gillet, 1907. G – elytron of S. naxiorum Král & Rejsek, 2000 with weakly and sparsely punctate elytral striae and intervals weakly punctate. H–I – eye coloration in specimens of S. horaki Zídek & Pokorný, 2010: H – female; I – male." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4504898/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

